{
  "texts": [
    "Formally, let G be the adjacency matrix such that G ij = n if account i ∈ U shares links from source j ∈ D n times.",
    "Similar to previous algorithms, we assume that some accounts have credibility labels.",
    "HITSHITS [36] updates account and source scores according tou t+1 i = j∈D A ij d t j, (8)d t+1 j = i∈U A ij u t i,( 9)respectively, where A ij = 1 if G ij > 0 and zero otherwise.",
    "The scores are normalized after each step t. Co-HITSInformation about some high-credibility sources may be available.",
    "Co-HITS incorporates this information into the propagation to calculate node scores [37]."
  ]
}